<headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 28 at 6:53AM EDT  by NWS Cleveland</headline>
<description>...LOW VISIBILITY THIS MORNING DUE TO SMOKE AND FOG...
The combination of smoke from the Canadian wildfires and residual
fog across the region has led to widespread visibility restrictions
of one mile or less this morning. A haze will continue across the
region over the next couple of hours as smoke will be slow to mix
out. Motorists should use caution while driving this morning
through the hazy conditions.
Smoke across the region has also led to poor air quality. Consult
your local health departments for more information on Air Quality
safety precautions.</description>
